This paper deals with the problem of Multi-Agent Path Finding (MAPF) with the additional constraint of deadlines, which is a common problem in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes two classes of optimal algorithms, which involve flow problems and combinatorial search algorithms, respectively, indicating a focus on mathematical optimization and algorithm design. The problem of MAPF-DL also involves multiple agents (cs.MA) and collision avoidance (cs.DS), which are important subfields of computer science. Finally, the empirical results presented in the paper involve comparisons between different solvers, indicating a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
